@{fg shine}PGP@{fg text}

                        Phil's Pretty Good Software
                                  Presents

                                  =======
                                  PGP(tm)
                                  =======

                          Pretty Good(tm) Privacy
                    Public Key Encryption for the Masses

Synopsis:   PGP(tm)  uses  public-key  encryption to protect E-mail and data
files.   Communicate  securely  with people you've never met, with no secure
channels  needed for prior exchange of keys.  PGP is well featured and fast,
with sophisticated key management, digital signatures, data compression, and
good ergonomic design.


Software  and  documentation (c) Copyright 1990-1996 Philip Zimmermann.  All
